Help
 
Page Up/Down = Scroll text
 
ESC = Preface / Chronology of St Francis / Abbreviations and Bibliography /
      Options / Credits / Quit
 
F1  = Display this screen
F2  = Display history information
F3  = Display layout information
F4  = Display artwork information
F5  = Display narratives information
F6  = Display nave information
F7  = Display transept information
F8  = Display apse information
F9  = Display vault information
F10 = Display window information
F11 = Cycle screen resolution (use Shift+F11 to cycle backwards)
F12 = Quit
 
Alt + Return = Toggle full screen video mode
 
Right mouse click = Toggle hotspot mode on/off
 
Left mouse click = Display hotspot text
 
Tab = Toggle movement key sets (arrow keys or W/S/A/D)
 
P = Toggle 1st/3rd person view mode
 
+/= (plus or equals sign) = Take screenshot
    Screenshots are saved in the basilica install directory, typically
    C:\Program Files\Institute of Digital Theology\Basilica of St. Francis, 
    and are named 'screenshot0.png', 'screenshot1.png', and so on.
 
Shift + movement keys = Run
 
Space = Jump (if walk mode) / Move up (if fly mode)
 
Alt = Move down (if fly mode)
 
Home / End = Restart at main door / lower church entrance
 
Pause = Toggle sound on/off
 
Ctrl = Toggle fly/walk mode
 
1, 2, 3, 4 = Display maps/schemas: general layout / nave / apse / transept
